> Ever wanted to make a steakhouse-quality meal in your own kitchen but weren't sure where to start? We've got the ingredients and recipe for you; all you have to do is bring it to life. The beef is finished with a flavorful garlic herb butter that knocks everyone's socks off.

Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to upper position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Halve @Yukon Gold Potatoes{16%ounce} and @Sweet Potatoes{2} lengthwise, then cut into ⅓-inch-thick wedges (like steak fries). Toss in a #large bowl{} with 1 TBSP oil. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Spread out on a #baking sheet{}. Roast in #oven{} until lightly browned, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Halve and peel @Shallot{1}, then mince until you have 2 TBSP. Pick @Parsley{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; discard stems. Finely chop leaves. Halve @Heirloom Grape Tomatoes{4%ounce}. Halve or quarter any large @Mini Bell Peppers{6%ounce} through stem ends. Pat @Sirloin Steak{24%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

At about the same time that potatoes have roasted 15 minutes, heat a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{7%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #plate{}, cover loosely with #foil{}, and let rest. Pour out any excess oil from pan and wipe clean.

Heat another drizzle of oil in pan used for steak over medium-high heat. Add mini bell peppers. Cook, tossing, until slightly softened and starting to char, ~{4-5%minutes}. Toss in tomatoes and cook until softened and their juices begin to release, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove from pan and set aside in a #medium bowl{}.

Rinse out pan and wipe dry with a paper towel. Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium heat. Add minced shallot. Cook, tossing, until softened and translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in ¼ cup water and @Beef Demi-Glace{1}, then bring to a boil. Let reduce slightly, about ~{2%minutes}. Remove pan from heat. Add half the parsley and @Butter{1%tablespoon} (save the garlic herb butter for the next step). Stir to melt.

Slice steak against the grain. Stir any juices released by steak into sauce in pan. Divide potatoes, veggies, and steak between plates. Spoon sauce over steak and dollop with @Garlic Herb Butter{1%ounce}, if desired. Sprinkle with remaining parsley and serve.

> If pan is dry when cooking peppers, add 1-2 TBSP water.